A memorial service for the late Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu is being held in Melrose Arch today. He passed away last week after battling lung cancer since 2018. JOHANNESBURG - A memorial service for the late Auditor-General, Kimi Makwetu will be held in Melrose Arch on Tuesday afternoon. Makwetu died last week after battling lung cancer since 2018. READ: Kimi Makwetu to be laid to rest Thursday He has been described as a deeply committed and humble person who wanted to serve. Makwetu was due to leave his position at the end of November, after almost seven-years in the office.